comment: Specified where the PowerMock Maven repo is, since it is not in Maven Central.
Created own rule ExpectedException to make code more compact and readable.
* Changed contract of AssertionErrorFactory to take a Description instead of String in method 'newAssertionError'. * Replaced DescriptionFormatter with Formatter. * Wrote more tests
Cleaning up code to make it more testable. Wrote more tests.
Refactoring ToString class into smaller, more manageable units.

* Implemented CollectionAssert.contains(Object[]) * Made CollectionAssert an ObjectGroupAssert, instead of just a GroupAssert * Finally added starting point of fluent interface: class Assertions

Made some progress with CollectionAssert.containsOnly(Object...) but not there yet.
Wrote some infrastructure code that verifies if an object is null or an empty group of values.

Reworking naming of classes and methods.

Working on IntegerAssert. Cleaned up code and tests.
Working on making ErrorMessage an interface, and the current ErrorMessage class an implementation of such interface under the name BasicErrorMessage.

Made factory methods of implementations of ErrorMessage more type-safe.
Making progress with IntegerAssert. Added overloaded methods that take "int".

Replaced Offset with Delta. Renamed Delta to Offset.
Replaced Offset with Delta. Renamed Delta to Offset.
Ensured that values passed to Offset are non-null and positive. Made constructor private, to force usage of static factory methods.
Working on ImageAssert. Changed Offset so it can take zero as value.
Implemented DoubleAssert. Minor changes in TestData.
Added more tests to package org.fest.assertions.data.
Implementing Ansgar's clever approach for "self types". Loving it!
